{
  "_readme": [
    "Source of truth for Shop product images. Each product gets a UNIQUE image.",
    "",
    "Fields per product:",
    "  photoId  (optional) — Unsplash photo ID (e.g. '1620799140408-edc6dcb6d633').",
    "                        When set, the fetch script pulls this exact image.",
    "  keywords (required) — comma-separated search terms used as a FALLBACK when",
    "                        photoId is missing or fails (via source.unsplash.com).",
    "",
    "How to run: node scripts/fetch-product-images.mjs",
    "  - Downloads each image to public/products/<productId>.jpg",
    "  - Skips files that already exist (safe to re-run).",
    "  - Prints a summary and, on 100% success, rewrites data/products.json",
    "    to reference /products/<productId>.jpg.",
    "",
    "If any product fails, edit its entry below (fix the photoId or keywords)",
    "and re-run the script. Only the failed ones will be re-fetched."
